   "source": [
    "ssarslt<-ssa(pmeanf, kind=\"2d-ssa\",L=c(8,8))\n",
    "plot(ssarslt,type=\"vectors\")\n",
    "decomprslt<-reconstruct(ssarslt,groups=list(LF=c(5,6,7,8),HF=c(1,2,3,4)))\n",
    "plot(decomprslt)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "990294f6-a259-4777-9cfa-56a52432096f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "`-` We set the window size to 8*8, so it produced an appropriate result."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "5b51a3c4-7619-4b97-b1dc-d9fdc21db85c",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "`-` It is important to choose the appropriate window size.\n",
    " - The window size must be large enough to properly decompose the global structure (=low freq).\n",
    " - At the same time, the window should be small enough to sharply detect the area where frequency change occurs."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "6523ccc7-4a75-4fe2-8bce-08421301e013",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 2D-PCA"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 216,
   "id": "8b92484a-b483-4be1-ad55-887167dc4d01",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "A=pmeanf\n",
    "G=t(A-mean(A))%*%(A-mean(A)) \n",
    "svd_<-svd(G)"
   ]
  },
